statement_informal:
Acyclicity implies $\mathrm{corr}(f) = -1/3$. If $f$ is $\pm 1$-valued and acyclic, then $\mathrm{corr}(f) = -1/3$.

\emph{Proof sketch:}
\begin{enumerate}
  \item For any $\pm 1$ triple $(a,b,c)$ avoiding the two all-equal cycles,
        $ab + bc + ac = -1$.
  \item Summing over all $6^n$ profiles:
        $\sum_p (f_{\!ab}\cdot f_{\!bc} + f_{\!bc}\cdot f_{\!ca} + f_{\!ab}\cdot f_{\!ca}) = -6^n$.
  \item Each pairwise expected product equals $\mathrm{corr}(f)$, so
        $3\cdot\mathrm{corr}(f) = -1$, giving $\mathrm{corr}(f) = -1/3$.
\end{enumerate}

$ab$--$bc$ kernel. Specialization of the general kernel to the $ab$--$bc$ vote pair: for all
$S,T\subseteq[n]$,
\[
  \Bigl(\tfrac16\Bigr)^{\!n}\sum_{p}
    \chi_S(\mathrm{abVotes}(p))\,\chi_T(\mathrm{bcVotes}(p))
  \;=\;
  \begin{cases} (-1/3)^{|S|} & S = T \\ 0 & S\ne T. \end{cases}
\]

$ab$--$ca$ kernel. Specialization of the general kernel to the $ab$--$ca$ vote pair: for all
$S,T\subseteq[n]$,
\[
  \Bigl(\tfrac16\Bigr)^{\!n}\sum_{p}
    \chi_S(\mathrm{abVotes}(p))\,\chi_T(\mathrm{caVotes}(p))
  \;=\;
  \begin{cases} (-1/3)^{|S|} & S = T \\ 0 & S\ne T. \end{cases}
\]

$bc$--$ca$ kernel. Specialization of the general kernel to the $bc$--$ca$ vote pair: for all
$S,T\subseteq[n]$,
\[
  \Bigl(\tfrac16\Bigr)^{\!n}\sum_{p}
    \chi_S(\mathrm{bcVotes}(p))\,\chi_T(\mathrm{caVotes}(p))
  \;=\;
  \begin{cases} (-1/3)^{|S|} & S = T \\ 0 & S\ne T. \end{cases}
\]

