statement_informal:
Character under a single bit flip. Flipping coordinate $i$ negates $\chi_S$ when $i\in S$ and leaves it unchanged
otherwise:
\[
  \chi_S(x^i) \;=\;
  \begin{cases} -\chi_S(x) & i\in S,\\ \chi_S(x) & i\notin S. \end{cases}
\]

Sum of a character over the cube. Summing the character $\chi_S$ over the whole hypercube yields
\[
  \sum_{x\in\{0,1\}^n} \chi_S(x) \;=\;
  \begin{cases} 2^n & S = \varnothing,\\ 0 & S\ne\varnothing. \end{cases}
\]

Completeness kernel for the Walsh basis. For points $x, y\in\{0,1\}^n$,
\[
  \sum_{S\subseteq[n]} \chi_S(x)\,\chi_S(y) \;=\;
  \begin{cases} 2^n & x = y,\\ 0 & x\ne y. \end{cases}
\]
This is the completeness kernel underlying Fourier inversion.

Distance equals minimum nonzero weight. If $C$ is linear (witnessed by some generator matrix) and has minimum distance $d$, then:
\begin{itemize}
  \item every nonzero codeword in $C$ has weight at least $d$;
  \item some codeword in $C$ has weight exactly $d$.
\end{itemize}

Probability of low-weight codeword. For any nonzero $x\in\alpha^k$,
\[
\frac{|\{G : \mathrm{wt}(Gx) < d\}|}{|\alpha|^{nk}}
\;\le\;
\frac{|B_{d-1}(\mathbf{0})|}{|\alpha|^n}.
\]

Pointwise characterization of composition. The composition $\mathrm{composeRestr}\,\rho_1\,\rho_2$ equals $\sigma$ if and only if
for every coordinate $i$ the value $(\rho_1\,i)$, falling back to $(\rho_2\,i)$,
equals $\sigma\,i$.

Encoder $\gamma$ preserves $\sigma$ at non-free variables. If $\rho_0\,v \neq \mathrm{none}$ (so $v$ is non-free), then the first component
$\gamma$ of the encoder loop SwitchingLemma2.razborovEncode's \texttt{go}
returns $\sigma\,v$ at $v$; the encoder does not alter $\sigma$ on non-free variables.

formal_statement:
import Mathlib

open Classical

namespace SwitchingLemma2
variable {n : ℕ}
abbrev Restriction (n : ℕ) := Fin n → Option Bool
end SwitchingLemma2

namespace SwitchingLemma2.Restriction
variable {n : ℕ}
def extend {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) (x : Fin n → Bool) : Fin n → Bool :=
  fun i => (ρ i).getD (x i)
end SwitchingLemma2.Restriction

namespace SwitchingLemma2.Restriction
variable {n : ℕ}
def freeVars {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) : Finset (Fin n) :=
  Finset.univ.filter (fun i => (ρ i).isNone)
end SwitchingLemma2.Restriction

namespace SwitchingLemma2
variable {n : ℕ}
private lemma extend_update_self {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) (v : Fin n)
    (x : Fin n → Bool) (b : Bool) (hv : v ∈ ρ.freeVars) (hxv : x v = b) :
    Restriction.extend (Function.update ρ v (some b)) x = ρ.extend x := sorry
end SwitchingLemma2

import Mathlib

open Classical

namespace SwitchingLemma2
variable {n : ℕ}
abbrev Restriction (n : ℕ) := Fin n → Option Bool
end SwitchingLemma2

namespace SwitchingLemma2.Restriction
variable {n : ℕ}
def freeVars {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) : Finset (Fin n) :=
  Finset.univ.filter (fun i => (ρ i).isNone)
end SwitchingLemma2.Restriction

namespace SwitchingLemma2.Restriction
variable {n : ℕ}
def numFree {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) : ℕ := ρ.freeVars.card
end SwitchingLemma2.Restriction

namespace SwitchingLemma2
variable {n : ℕ}
private lemma numFree_update_le {n : ℕ} (ρ : Restriction n) (v : Fin n) (b : Bool) :
    Restriction.numFree (Function.update ρ v (some b)) ≤ ρ.numFree := sorry
end SwitchingLemma2

